        "score": 0.41207963,
        "text": "The document outlines inspection fees and related costs for Transmission Service Providers (TSPs) and Resource Entities associated with the Electric Reliability Council of Texas (ERCOT). Key points include:\n\n1. **Inspection Fees**: \n   - TSPs must pay $4,500 for each inspected substation or switching station.\n   - Resource Entities, excluding federally owned ones, pay fees based on their MW capacity relative to aggregate capacity, calculated semiannually.\n\n2. **Calculation and Invoicing**:\n   - ERCOT calculates fees twice a year, using MW capacity data from the last 15 business days of the period.\n   - Invoices are issued semiannually in January and July, with a 30-day payment deadline. Late payments incur 18% annual interest and are reported to the Public Utility Commission of Texas.\n\n3. **Additional Fees**:\n   - Voluminous copy fee: $0.15 per page over 50 pages.\n   - Information request costs: Actual costs estimated by ERCOT, requiring pre-approval and payment by the requester.\n   - ERCOT labor costs: $15 per hour for information requests deemed burdensome.\n\nThese fees and processes are part of ERCOT's regulatory framework to ensure compliance and operational readiness.",
        "metadata": {
