        }
      },
      {
        "id": "08c45e1f-825a-47af-af51-88a14ed2acd1",
        "score": 0.35004127,
        "text": "The document outlines procedures related to the ERCOT (Electric Reliability Council of Texas) system management activities, specifically focusing on network operations model changes. Key points include:\n\n1. **Interconnection Agreements**: Southern Cross must provide ERCOT with funds covering the entire project cost and sign an interconnection agreement with a Transmission Service Provider (TSP). ERCOT must receive a notice to proceed with construction and financial security details.\n\n2. **Review and Approval Process**: Upon receiving necessary information, ERCOT will review and notify the requester of any required modifications. ERCOT may request further details and will approve or reject requests within 15 days. Approved changes will be published for TSPs and DCTOs.\n\n3. **Periodic Updates**: ERCOT will perform periodic updates to the Network Operations Model. Market participants must provide updates for planned transmission and resource construction a year in advance. Timely submission of changes is required.\n\n4. **Technical Information Submission**: For any facility addition, revision, or deletion, all technical modeling information must be submitted to ERCOT.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Nodal_Protocols:_Section_3:_Management_Activities_for_the_ERCOT_System/page_158.jpg",
          "page_num": 158,
          "title": "ERCOT Nodal Protocols: Section 3: Management Activities for the ERCOT System",
