        "text": "The document outlines procedures related to customer registration and scheduling for the Electric Reliability Council of Texas (ERCOT). It details the evaluation processes for move-in and move-out dates in relation to switch dates and mass transition drop dates:\n\n1. **Move In After Switch Date (15.1.6.4):** ERCOT evaluates two Retail Business Days before the scheduled move-in meter read date or upon receiving the TDSP response. If the move-in date is after a switch date, both processes run concurrently.\n\n2. **Move In After Mass Transition Drop Date (15.1.6.5):** Similar to the above, evaluations occur two Retail Business Days prior. If the move-in date is after a mass transition drop date, both processes run concurrently.\n\n3. **Move Out Date Prior to or Equal to Switch Date (15.1.6.6):** Evaluations occur two Retail Business Days before the scheduled move-out date. If a switch is scheduled with a date after or equal to the move-out date, the switch is canceled by ERCOT.\n\n4. **Move Out Date After Switch Date (15.1.6.7):** Evaluations occur two Retail Business Days before the scheduled move-out date. If the move-out date is after a switch date, both processes run concurrently. If the submitting CR is not the CR of Record, the move-out is canceled.\n\n5. **Move Out Date After Mass Transition Drop Date (15.1.6.8):** Similar to the above, evaluations occur two Retail Business Days prior. If the move-out date is after a mass transition drop date, both processes run concurrently. If the submitting CR is not the CR of Record, the move-out is canceled.",
