        "text": "The document page outlines procedures related to Securitization Uplift Charges in the context of electricity market operations. Key points include:\n\n1. **Opt-Out Entities**: Transmission-voltage customers of a REP (Retail Electric Provider) who opt out will have specific ESI IDs included in the Adjusted Metered Load (AML) adjustments. These are based on notifications filed by a deadline in a specific PUCT project.\n\n2. **Return of Securitization Proceeds**: If a Load-Serving Entity (LSE) is required to return securitization proceeds, it must remit these to its Qualified Scheduling Entity (QSE) within two business days. The QSE then sends the funds to ERCOT for payment of Securitization Uplift Charge Invoices.\n\n3. **Securitization Uplift Charge Calculation**: ERCOT allocates charges to QSEs representing LSEs. The charge for each QSE on an operating day is calculated using a formula involving several variables, such as DQSELERS and DERCOTQSELERS. Definitions for these variables are provided, including LASUCAMT, which represents the charge allocated to each QSE.\n\nThe document is part of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, effective October 1, 2024.",
