        "score": 0.57376504,
        "text": "The document outlines procedures related to Securitization Uplift Charges by ERCOT. Key points include:\n\n1. **Estimation and Calculation**: ERCOT estimates under-collections or over-collections for the current or upcoming evaluation period and calculates the periodic billing requirement, considering prior and anticipated amounts. This determines the Securitization Uplift Charge Daily Amount for future billing.\n\n2. **Re-estimation Process**: If a revision is needed, ERCOT will notify Market Participants 15 days before the new charge becomes effective.\n\n3. **Payment Responsibilities**: Load Serving Entities (LSEs) not opting out must pay their share of the charge based on their Adjusted Metered Load. The charge is not passed to transmission-voltage customers who opt out.\n\n4. **Invoice Preparation**: ERCOT prepares initial invoices using settlement data and posts them on the Market Information System (MIS) on the same day as Real-Time Market Initial Statements. The publication can occur as late as midnight on the scheduled date.\n\n5. **Payment and Access**: Invoice recipients must pay any net debit by the due date, regardless of disputes. They are responsible for accessing invoices on the MIS Certified Area.\n\nOverall, the document details the process for calculating, notifying, invoicing, and paying Securitization Uplift Charges.",
