        "text": "The document is from Section 5 of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, focusing on Transmission Security Analysis and Reliability Unit Commitment. It outlines procedures for Qualified Scheduling Entities (QSEs) regarding the submission and updating of verifiable cost data for resources. Key points include:\n\n1. **Submission of Verifiable Costs**: QSEs can submit data from resources as verifiable costs at any time, and this data will be considered by ERCOT. A Power Purchase Agreement (PPA) is not required for this submission.\n\n2. **Notification for Updates**: ERCOT will notify a QSE to update verifiable cost data if a resource receives more than 50 RUC instructions in a year or if at least five years have passed since the last approval.\n\n3. **Submission Deadlines**: QSEs must submit updated verifiable cost data within 30 days of receiving a notice from ERCOT. Failure to do so will result in the use of generic cost caps until updated data is approved.\n\n4. **Exclusions**: Energy Storage Resources (ESRs) are excluded from submitting verifiable costs.\n\n5. **Verifiable Startup Costs**: Details the calculation of startup costs for resources, including fuel consumption rates and associated costs, as per the Verifiable Cost Manual.\n\nThis section ensures that ERCOT maintains accurate and up-to-date cost data for resource management and operational efficiency.",
